title.narrative: EARLY CHILDHOOD

description.narrative: By 2024 educational agents working with early childhood have the strengthened capacity to provide quality education., which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, more early childhood children, children with disabilities, adolescents from trade schools and children and adolescents living in territories vulnerable to disasters have inclusive, quality and relevant education, even in emergencies or disasters.

description.narrative: UNICEF Cuba has contributed to strengthening the capacities of 8,042 educators from the social and community program “Educate Your Child” across the country, to support early childhood stimulation, as well as developing an advocacy toolkit for the extension of “Casitas Infantiles” (Workplace Day Care Centers), as an institutional way of providing educational care to this age group. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2022
